name: code
title: Code
help: The account code is usually a number (e.g. : 101000). The account code help to locate the account in the chart of account. This code must be unique per company account chart.

name: parent
title: Parent Account
help: The parent account helps to define the company chart of accounts. Depending on the company field, you will be only entitled to select parent accounts associated to the same company.

name: accountType
title: Account Type
help: The account type is an attribute attached to the account that will impact the way accounting documents will be printed or filtered. Account Types are as follow : asset, cash, commitment, current asset (stock), debt, equity, expense, immobilisation, income, payable, provision, receivable, special, tax, view

name: reconcileOk
title: Reconcilable ?
help: The checkbox reconcilable helps to filter, within the reconcile interface the entrylines to reconcile. The accounts of type receivable and payable will usually be ticked as reconcilable.

name: company
title: Company
help: Each account is linked to a chart of account through the field Parent, and to a company.

name: typeSelect
title: Type
doc: The account management lines is the basis of account configuration. The accounting configuration can be applied to 3 types of elements : product (including familyProduct),tax and payments.  When a new line is created within the table of one of those object, the type is attributed automatically, otherwise you have to set a type manually as this field is required.

name: company
title: Company
help: Select the company concerned by the account configuration.
help_t: Sélectionner la société concernée par cette configuration
doc: The accounting configuration is specific to each company of the system. The system will by default fill in the company with your user active company.

name: purchaseAccount
title: Purchase account
help: Account of type Expense to select within the company account chart.
help_t: Compte de charges à sélectionner parmi de le plan comptable de la société sélectionnée.
doc: The purchase account is used when validating a supplier invoice/refund while generating move/move lines. The system will only allow to select accounts of type Expense and belonging to the company chart (check field company of this form).

name: saleAccount
title: Sale account
help: Account of type Income to select within the company account chart.
help_t: Compte de produit à sélectionner parmi de le plan comptable de la société sélectionnée.
doc: The sale account is used when validating a customer invoice/refund while generating move/move lines. The system will only allow to select accounts of type Income and belonging to the company chart (check field company of this form).

name: purchaseVat
title: Purchase V.A.T.
doc: This field defines the default VAT value used when selecting a product while creating a purchase order, or a supplier invoice/refund. But the VAT can also apply on top elements such as productFamily to avoid configuring it several times.

name: saleVat
title: Sale V.A.T.
doc: This field defines the default VAT value used when selecting a product while creating a sale order, or a customer invoice/refund. But the VAT can also apply on top elements such as productFamily to avoid configuring it several times. VAT configuration can also be set on taxes.

name: cashAccount
title: Payment account
help: Account of type Cash to select within the company account chart.
help_t: Compte de liquidité à sélectionner parmi de le plan comptable de la société sélectionnée.
doc: The payment account is used when validating a payment while generating move/movelines. The system will only allow to select accounts of type cash.

name: taxAccount
title: Tax account
help: Account to select within the company account chart (usually a receivable or payable)
help_t: Compte à sélectionner parmi de le plan comptable de la société sélectionnée (en général un compte de tiers)
doc: The tax account is used when validating a customer or supplier invoice/refund while generating move/move lines. The system will only allow to select accounts belonging to the company chart (check field company of this form).

name: product
title: Product
help: Product concerned by the configuration.
doc: The field product associates the account configuration to the product. /n Account configurations are all listed in the tab Accounting, table Accounts on the product. While creating an account configuration directly from the product, the product association and account type will be set by default and will not be displayed.

name: tax
title: Tax
help: Tax concerned by the configuration.

name: paymentMode
title: Payment mode
help: Payment mode concerned by the configuration.
help_t: Mode de paiement concerné par la configuration
doc: The field product associates the account configuration to the payment mode. /n Account configurations are all listed in the tab Accounting, table Accounts on the product. While creating an account configuration directly from the product, the product association and account type will be set by default and will not be displayed.

name: productFamily
title: Product family
help: Product Family concerned by the configuration.
help_t: Famille de produit concernée par la configuration.

title: Reference Due Date
title_t: Date d'échéance à prendre en compte

name: discountProduct
title: Discount product
help: Select the discount product amoung discount product list. This product will appear on the sales order or invoice unless the checkbox 'Same product' is ticked.
